CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782778699
OL,3,CIran's Strait of Hormuz warning casts
OL,4,Cdoubt on UK-France defensive mission
OL,6,FThe initial deal reached between the
OL,7,FUS and Iran ` known as the Islamabad
OL,8,Fmemorandum of understanding ` only
OL,9,Fsecures safe, toll-free passage of the
OL,10,Fstrait for 60 days, pending the
OL,11,Foutcome of a final agreement on
OL,12,FTehran's disputed nuclear plans.
OL,14,FAs part of opening up the waterway, it
OL,15,Fsaid demining would be carried out by
OL,16,FIran.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782778699
OL,3,CIran's Strait of Hormuz warning casts
OL,4,Cdoubt on UK-France defensive mission
OL,6,FThe initial pact also leaves it to
OL,7,FTehran and Oman, in conjunction with
OL,8,Fother Gulf states, to "define the
OL,9,Ffuture administration and maritime
OL,10,Fservices in the Strait of Hormuz".
OL,12,FIn the meantime, Iran has continued to
OL,13,Ftry and exert leverage over the
OL,14,Fchannel, including demanding ships
OL,15,Fseek permission to transit and raising
OL,16,Fthe spectre of future charges.
OL,18,FFollowing a meeting with the sultan of
OL,19,FOman in Paris, Mr Macron posted on X:
OL,20,F"We are working together for de-
OL,21,Fescalation in the Middle East.
OL,26,@pD@WOUrD@aO]|D@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782778699
OL,3,CIran's Strait of Hormuz warning casts
OL,4,Cdoubt on UK-France defensive mission
OL,6,F"We have decided to collaborate
OL,7,Fjointly, in co-ordination with our
OL,8,Fpartners, on demining the strait to
OL,9,Fsecure maritime routes and ensure free
OL,10,Fand unconditional passage through the
OL,11,FStrait of Hormuz."
OL,13,FIn reply, Mr Gharibabadi wrote:
OL,14,F"Macron has said that he is
OL,15,Fcooperating with his partners in
OL,16,Fdemining the Strait of Hormuz.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@RO]vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1782778699
OL,3,CIran's Strait of Hormuz warning casts
OL,4,Cdoubt on UK-France defensive mission
OL,6,F"According to the Islamabad memorandum
OL,7,Fof understanding, demining is carried
OL,8,Fout solely by Iran and by no other
OL,9,Fcountry, and we fundamentally do not
OL,10,Fpermit any such thing.
OL,12,F"The situation is sensitive and
OL,13,Fcomplex. We strongly advise France not
OL,14,Fto complicate it further with its
OL,15,Fprovocations."
OL,17,FThe UK Foreign Office has been
OL,18,Fcontacted for comment.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUwD@NO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
